About Configuration

The configuration in pytextedit, available from "Options -> Options" or by pressing F3, allows the user to change the interface and behavior of the program.

Font Options

* Name - Specifies the name of the font to use in the main text box.
* Size - Specifies the size of the font to use in the main text box. This must be a positive integer.
* Style - Specifies the style of the font to use in the main text box. 
* Foreground - Specifies the foreground (text) color to use in the main text box.
* Background - Specifies the background color to use in the main text box.
* Sel. Foreground - Specifies the foreground (text) color to use when text is selected in the main text box.
* Sel. Background - Specifies the background color to use when text is selected in the main text box.
* Text Wrap - Specifies the text wrap to use in the main text box. Text can wrap on the last character (char), on the last word (word), or not at all (none).

Interface Options

* UI Foreground - Specifies the foreground (text) color to use in the interface. Note that this is different from the Foreground option in the Font tab.
* UI Background - Specifies the background color to use in the interface. Note that this is different from the Background option in the Font tab.
* Toolbar - Specifies whether the toolbar should be displayed.
* Toolbar Buttons - Specifies whether the buttons on the toolbar should use text, images, or both.
* Toolbar Images - Specifies where in relation to the text the images on the toolbar buttons should be shown. This is only relevant if the Toolbar Buttons option is set to both.
* Toolbar Image Size - Specifies whether the images on the toolbar buttons should be large or small.
* Line Numbers - Specifies whether the line number should be displayed.
* Status Bar - Specifies whether the status bar should be displayed.
* Command Bar - Specifies whether the command bar should be displayed.
* Documents List - Specifies whether the documents list should be displayed.
* Documents List Width - Specifies the width (in characters) of the documents list.
* Title - Specifies whether the title should display the just the filename or the full path and filename.
* Highlight Line - Specifies whether the current line will be highlighted.
* Highlight Line Color - Specifies the color used for highlighting the current line.

Editing Options

* Auto-Indent - Specifies whether the next line will be automatically indented based on the indentation of the previous line.
* Replace Tabs - Specifies whether tab characters will be automatically replaced with spaces.
* Indent Amount - Specifies the indent amount. This must be a positive integer.
* Spaces Per Tab - Specifies how many spaces are in a tab, for when automatically replacing tabs. This must be a positive integer.
* Reverse Separator - Specifies the separator used when reversing lines.
* Join Separator - Specifies the separator used when joining lines.
* "Smart" Home - Specifies whether "smart" home will be enabled. When enabled pressing the Home key will move to the first position after any indentation.
* "Smart" End - Specifies whether "smart" end will be enabled. When enabled pressing the End key will move to the last position before any indentation.
* Auto-Strip - Specifies whether extra whitespace at the end of a line will be automatically removed.
* Duplicate Line - Specifies whether duplicated lines will be positioned above or below the current line.
* Prepend To Line - Specifies a string to automatically prepend to the start of a line.
* Append To Line - Specifies a string to automatically append to the end of a line.
* Auto-Wrap - Specifies whether automatic line wrapping will be enabled.
* Auto-Wrap Length - Specifies the length of lines necessary for them to automatically wrap.

Searching Options

* Case Sensitivity - Specifies whether searches are case sensitive by default.
* Regex Search - Specifies whether searches use regular expressions by default.
* Cursor Position - Specifies whether the cursor will be positioned at the start or end of a string that has been found.
* Keep Dialog Open - Specifies whether the dialog will be kept open after a search by default.
* Negative Lines in Goto - Specifies how negative lines in Goto will be treated. It can go that many lines from the end, from the beginning, or simply ignore negative values.
* Advanced Search Commands - Specifies whether more advanced commands in the Search menu will be shown.
* Remember Find History - Specifies whether Find will remember the history.
* Remember Replace History - Specifies whether Replace will remember the history.
* Search History Order - Specifies whether the Find and Replace history will be shown oldest first or last.

Network Options

* Email Server - Specifies the default email server.
* Email Sender - Specifies the default email sender.
* Email Recipient - Specifies the default email recipient.
* FTP Server - Specifies the default FTP server.
* Collab. Editing Server - Specifies the default collaborative editing server.
* Collab. Editing Port - Specifies the default collaborative editing port.

File Browser Options

* Title - Specifies whether the title will display the current directory or simply "File Browser".
* Toolbar - Specifies whether the toolbar will be displayed.
* Toolbar Buttons - Specifies whether the buttons on the toolbar should use text, images, or both.
* Toolbar Images - Specifies where in relation to the text the images on the toolbar buttons should be shown. This is only relevant if the Toolbar Buttons option is set to both.
* Menu Bar - Specifies whether the menu bar will be displayed.
* File Menu - Specifies whether the File menu will be displayed.
* Folders Menu - Specifies whether the Folders menu will be displayed.
* Context Menu - Specifies whether the context menu will be displayed.
* Sort Alphabetically - Specifies whether the files and folders should be sorted alphabetically.
* Folder Position - Specifies whether the folders should be displayed above or below the files.

Menu Options

* Menu Bar - Specifies whether the menu bar will be shown.
* Tear-off Menus - Specifies whether tear-off menus will be enabled. If enabled, menus can be "torn" off from the main application and become separate windows.
* Menu Icons - Specifies whether icons will be shown in the menus.
* File Menu  - Specifies whether the File menu will be displayed.
* Edit Menu  - Specifies whether the Edit menu will be displayed.
* Documents Menu  - Specifies whether the Documents menu will be displayed.
* Search Menu  - Specifies whether the Search menu will be displayed.
* Tools Menu  - Specifies whether the Tools menu will be displayed.
* Code Menu  - Specifies whether the Code menu will be displayed.
* Options Menu  - Specifies whether the Options menu will be displayed.
* Help Menu  - Specifies whether the Help menu will be displayed.
* Context Menu  - Specifies whether the context menu will be displayed.

Macro Options

* Command Bar - Specifies whether the command bar will run macro commands or Python statements.
* Run Command - Specifies whether Run Command will run macro commands or Python statements.
* Error on Unknown Commands - Specifies whether unknown commands will cause errors or fail silently.
* Stop on Error - Specifies whether execution of a macro will stop when an error occurs.
* Allow Python Statements - Specifies whether Python statements are allowed in a macro.
* Allow Variables - Specifies whether variables are allowed in a macro.
* Comment Start - Specifies the string used to start a comment. It is not recommended to change this.
* Variable Start - Specifies the string used to start a variable. It is not recommended to change this. Note that this must be a single character.
* Python Statement Start - Specifies the string used to start a Python statement. It is not recommended to change this.

Code Options

* Python Interpreter - Specifies the command used for running Python code.
* Perl Interpreter - Specifies the command used for running Perl code.
* PHP Interpreter - Specifies the command used for running PHP code.
* C Compiler - Specifies the command used for compiling C code.
* C++ Compiler - Specifies the command used for compiling C++ code.
* Java Compiler - Specifies the command used for compiling Java code.
* Prompt for Arguments - Specifies whether the user will be prompted for command line arguments when running or compiling code.
* Block Indenting - Specifies whether automatic block indenting will be enabled for C code, Python code, or if it will be disabled.
* Comment Continuation - Specifies whether comments will be automatically continued for Python-style comments, for C++-style comments, or if it will be disabled.

Misc Options

* Initial Directory - Specifies the initial directory used when displaying the open and save dialogs. Set to "$HOME" for it to be automatically set to your home directory after a restart.
* Default Encoding - Specifies the default encoding. Set to "DEFAULT" for it to be automatically replaced with the system default.
* Prompt For Encoding - Specifies whether the user will be prompted for the encoding before the default encodings are tried.
* Date Format - Specifies the format used when inserting dates.
* Time Format - Specifies the format used when inserting times.
* Restore Last Open - Specifies whether the file will be automatically reopened next session.
* Save Window Geometry - Specifies whether the window size and position on exit will be saved and restored next session.
* Save Cursor Mode - Specifies whether the cursor mode on exit will be saved and restored next session.
* Confirm on Exit - Specifies whether a confirmation dialog will be shown on exit if there are unsaved changes.
* Font Size Change - Specifies how much the font size should be changed when enlarging or shrinking.
* Fast Scroll Lines - Specifies how many lines fast scrolling should scroll by.
* Page Scroll Lines - Specifies how many lines PageUp and PageDown will be scrolled by.
* Copy/Cut Line - Specifies whether the current line will be copied or cut if nothing is selected.